## Ground rules (apply everywhere)

- The publishable key (`pk_...`) is safe to ship inside an app. Secret
  keys (`sk_...`) and personal access tokens (`moth_pat_...`) are
  server-side credentials — never put them in app code, never commit them.
- Google client IDs reach the app at runtime via the project config RPC —
  never hardcode them in Dart code.
- All admin state lives server-side. The CLI and the admin SPA drive the
  same `moth.admin.v1` RPCs, so anything scripted here is inspectable in
  the SPA and vice versa.
- Every CLI command accepts `--json` for parseable output on stdout;
  errors go to stderr with a non-zero exit code.
